Package models

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Booking
    A booking of a screening of a movie.
    BookingDAO
    The Data access object responsible for getting and saving the Booking data.
    Customer
    A customer wanting to book a movie.
    CustomerDAO
    The Data access object responsible for getting and saving the Customer data.
    DBModel
    Defines that all database models should have an idea where the client API has the ability to get and set this id.
    Employee
    An employee wanting to manage the cinema.
    EmployeeDAO
    The Data access object responsible for getting and saving the Employee data.
    Film
    Contains the properties corresponding to the columns in the database for the film.
    FilmDAO
    The Data access object responsible for getting and saving the Film data.
    PaymentInfo
    Contains the credit card information and the price.
    Screening
    The screening of the film.
    ScreeningDAO
    The Data access object responsible for getting and saving the Screening data.
    Seat
    A seat within the cinema room.
    SeatDAO
    The Data access object responsible for getting and saving the Seat data.
    User
    Defines the structure used for the Customer and Employee models.
